Description: The rest on the flight into Egypt with an angel pulling down a palm frond Etching
Curator's comments: As pointed out by Tomasz Sioda (email 28 March 2013) this impression represents an unidentified state as indicated by the monogram 'W' on the stone lower left, hitherto unnoticed. This print was issued as a black and white facsimile by the British Museum in 'Reproductions of Prints in the British Museum', Third Series Part II (Specimens of Etching by Italian Masters 1525-1550), Published by the Trustees, in 1908 where it was number XX and described there as 'Simone Cantarini. The Rest in Egypt.'; see 1908,0622.3.23 (Shelfmark 245*.b.31).
Bibliographic references: Massari 1997 / In 'Simone Cantarini detto il Pesarese', ed. Andrea Emiliani (18.I)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (With Philipe's blindstamp and initials CMC)
